{
  "stem": "2718.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So from then on, the-- the ghettos were set up, and-- and people-- almost, I would say, without an exception-- would-- they had to go and move into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the ghetto was meant that they left their houses, with everything in it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "All we could take was-- we couldn't take [? anything ?] anyway, because it was too small, one family in one room, with four of us.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Four-- four-- four of us, my mother, my father, my sister, and myself.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were lucky to have a room to ourselves in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "People moved out from there, whoever lived there before, they-- they-- I don't know where they put them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they built-- they put barbed wire around the ghetto, like every other ghetto probably.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And you had to have a pass to come in and out of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, again, at that time, food was starting to get short, and there were coupons issued for-- for anybody who was alive, whether he was a worker or a-- a-- hard labor worker, or office worker-- there were different type of coupons.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "People who were-- who were useful, they were issued a bigger ration.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "People who were older, or children-- I'm talking about everybody, not only Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But Jews, particularly, were-- were deprived of-- of-- of food, which the non-Jews had the chance, or had the ability to, because we were in ghettos already at that time.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were very lucky because, on the 19th of March, at the same time, it was a disaster and a-- and a catastrophe for the whole Hungarian Jewish world.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Our factory was manufacturing parts which was important for the German army-- as little as it was, but they-- they thought it was important enough.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
